### E-D1 unclosed
markup:1:1: '<menu>' was never closed (E-D1)
<menu>
^

### E-D1 mismatched close
markup:1:1: '<menu>' opened here is closed by '</flex>' (E-D1)
<menu>
^

### E-D1 stray close
markup:1:1: unexpected '</' with no open tag (E-D1)
</menu>
^

### E-D2 missing =
markup:1:8: attribute 'placeholder' is missing '=' (E-D2)
<input placeholder/>
       ^

### E-D2 unterminated literal
markup:1:21: unterminated "..." for attribute 'value' (E-D2)
<input value="oops/>
                    ^

### E-D2 reserved separator byte
markup:1:16: reserved separator byte in attribute literal (E-D2)
<input value="ab"/>
               ^

### E-D2 unterminated hole
markup:1:7: unterminated '{{' binding hole (E-D2)
<flex>{{filename</flex>
      ^

### E-D2 id expr
markup:1:7: 'id' takes a "name", not {expr} (E-D2)
<flex id={x}></flex>
      ^

### E-D2 on: literal
markup:1:9: 'on:press' handler must be {expr} (E-D2)
<button on:press="save">x</button>
        ^

### E-D3 unknown tag
markup:2:5: unknown tag '<nope>' (E-D3) — lowercase tags come from the registry; a user class is Capitalized at the dom! tier
    <nope/>
    ^

### E-D4 unknown attr + did-you-mean
markup:1:8: '<input>' has no attribute 'placholder' (did you mean 'placeholder'?) (E-D4)
<input placholder="x"/>
       ^

### E-D4 unknown attr no suggestion
markup:1:7: '<span>' has no attribute 'bogus' (E-D4)
<span bogus="1">x</span>
      ^

### E-D5 int
markup:1:7: attribute 'width="wide"' must be an integer (E-D5)
<flex width="wide"></flex>
      ^

### E-D5 bool
markup:1:11: attribute 'checked="maybe"' must be "true" or "false" (E-D5)
<checkbox checked="maybe"/>
          ^

### E-D5 enum align
markup:1:7: align="Wat" is not one of Start/Center/End/Stretch (E-D5)
<span align="Wat">x</span>
      ^

### E-D5 enum dock
markup:1:10: dock="Under" is not one of Top/Bottom/Left/Right/Fill (E-D5)
<spinner dock="Under"/>
         ^

### E-D6 theme
markup:1:7: theme="dark" is not supported yet (E-D6)
<flex theme="dark"></flex>
      ^

### E-D12 empty payload
markup is empty (E-D12: a node is required)

### id inside for
markup:1:28: 'id' is not allowed inside a $for body
<flex>$for p in xs { <span id="bad">x</span> }</flex>
                           ^

### for at top level
markup:1:1: '$for' needs an enclosing element at the dom! tier
$for p in xs { <span>x</span> }
^

### else without if
markup:1:7: unexpected '$else' with no matching '$if'
<flex>$else { <span>x</span> }</flex>
      ^

### for missing in
markup:1:16: '$for p' expected 'in'
<flex>$for p of xs { }</flex>
               ^

### unclosed block
markup:1:32: unexpected '</' inside a '{ }' block (missing '}')
<flex>$if cond { <span>x</span></flex>
                               ^

### leaf with element child
markup:1:9: <button> is a leaf and cannot hold element children
<button><span>x</span></button>
        ^

### for inside leaf
markup:1:9: '$for'/'$if' need a container tag, not leaf <button>
<button>$for p in xs { x }</button>
        ^

